<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="63" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5221/12</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Spanish Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Riaño</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-12"><hi rend="italic">February 12,
                                        1919</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 104</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: With reference to our
                                conversation of December 28th and under instructions received from
                                my Government, I have the honor to propose to Your Excellency to
                                cancel the denunciation of the Treaty of Friendship and General
                                Relations of July 3, 1902 by the Government of the United
                                    States<note n="60" xml:id="d63fn60">See <ref target="frus1918#pg_3"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                            Relations</hi>, 1918, pp. 3</ref> (footnote 2) and <ref target="frus1918#pg_10">10</ref>.</note> and to abrogate
                                instead Articles 23 and 24 of that Treaty.</p>
                            <p>Thanking Your Excellency for the early and favorable attention which,
                                I have no doubt, you will give to this matter, I gladly avail myself
                                [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>